snippet.title: Drake Drops Surprise Album & Disses Tyga for Kylie Jenner Relationship
snippet.description:
7 Things you don’t know about Nicki Minaj►►http://bit.ly/TflEB1
For all your music needs ►► http://bit.ly/ClevverMusic 

The Beyonce method strikes again! Drake just dropped a surprise album out of nowhere and it is chuck full of new material.  
The album is titled -  If You’re Reading This It’s Too Late -  and like Beyonce’s self-titled album, there was little to no promotional activity before the surprise release aside from an ambiguous 14 minute  teaser video titled “Jungle” in which Drake ponders about his life. 
The teaser prompted people to speculate that new music was coming but I don’t think anyone was expecting a surprise like this. 
In the Jungle teaser, lots of flashback footage is shown of Drake in his younger years back in his hometown of Toronto as well as in his LA acting days. It shows some of the struggles he endured growing up as well as in the midst of his fame and  gets rather introspective when Drake is heard saying QUOTE - "trying to balance my own sanity...I'm f--king drinking more, I'm smoking more. We're out here staying up so late it's early...I'm not losing it, though. I'm just venting. I'm just more worried about myself. I just gotta come home."
Now many of you Drake fans may remember that he did announce a new album titled Views From the 6 back in August but its unclear whether or not that could be a project he  is still working on or If Your Reading This Its Too Late is what Views From the 6 evolved into. Whichever way, we got new music. That’s really the biggest takeaway.
On a juicier note, many are pointing out the fact that Drake is not putting up any filters with these new rhymes including a dig that he throws at Tyga when he raps a line saying QUOTE – “Your content so aggressive lately, what’s irking you? Sh-t is getting so personal in your verses, too/ I want to prove that I’m number one over all these n—as/ Being number two is just being the first to lose.” This of course is in response to the constant riff that has been going on between these two for quite some time now. 
You can hear and sip all the tea Drake is dishing on this album now on itunes. 
So what do you guys think of the album so far and do you think pulling a Beyonce was the right move for this album? Sound off in the comment section below, don’t forget to subscribe and then click right over here to switch gears a little bit with a rundown of facts you may not know about Nicki Minaj. Thanks for watching Clevver Music, I’m Erin Robinson and I’ll see you next time.
